    &lt;CommentText&gt;Thank you for your comments regarding your experience at Manchester Royal Infirmary. Mrs Sophie Edwards, Unit Manager for the Outpatient Clinical Service Unit (CSU) apologises for your experience and the breakdown in communication in relation to the cancelled telephone consultation and subsequent discharge. Mrs Edwards encourages you to make contact with the PALS department which will enable her to review the circumstances around your discharge, revise your pathway as appropriate, and ensure that your contact details are correct on the hospital patient information system.

Therefore we would be grateful if you would contact the Patient Advice and Liaison Service (PALS) on 0161 276 8686 or by e-mailing pals@mft.nhs.uk quoting reference number PO20/0072 to discuss your experience in more detail. 

The Patient Experience Team
